y supports: ICRS Galactic sky coordinates angular separation sphere simple frame transformation ICRS Galactic Julian Date / Modified Julian Date conversion","code":""},{"path":"https://uskovgs.github.io/astrocoords/index.html","id":"installation","dir":"","previous_headings":"","what":"Installation","title":"Astronomical Coordinates for R","text":"can install development version astrocoords GitHub :","code":"# install.packages(\"pak\") pak::pak(\"uskovgs/astrocoords\")"},{"path":"https://uskovgs.github.io/astrocoords/index.html","id":"quick-examples","dir":"","previous_headings":"","what":"Quick examples","title":"Astronomical Coordinates for R","text":"Create coordinates ICRS frame: Transform Galactic coordinates: Measure angular separation arcseconds: Parse compact coordinate string: Work Julian Date:","code":"library(astrocoords) #>  #> Attaching package: 'astrocoords' #> The following object is masked from 'package:graphics': #>  #>     frame  x <- ra_dec(c(10, 20), c(30, 40)) x #> <sky_coord[2] icrs> #> [1] 00h40m00.0s +30°00'00\" 01h19m60.0s +40°00'00\" transform(x, galactic()) #> <sky_coord[2] galactic> #> [1] 119°59'08.0\" -32°48'23\" 128°50'58.6\" -22°32'36\" separation(ra_dec(10, 20), ra_dec(11, 21)) #> [1] 4932.552 parse_coord(\"J230631.0+155633\") #> <sky_coord[1] icrs> #> [1] 23h06m31.0s +15°56'33\" jd <- jd_fromdate(as.POSIXct(\"2026-03-08 12:34:56\", tz = \"UTC\")) jd #> [1] 2461108  jd2greg(jd, tz = \"UTC\") #> [1] \"2026-03-08 12:34:56 UTC\""},{"path":"https://uskovgs.github.io/astrocoords/reference/astrocoords-package.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"astrocoords: Astronomical Coordinates for R — astrocoords-package","title":"astrocoords: Astronomical Coordinates for R — astrocoords-package","text":"Vectorized astronomical coordinates R.","code":""},{"path":[]},{"path":"https://uskovgs.github.io/astrocoords/reference/astrocoords-package.html","id":"author","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Author","titl